flawed_nl_solution:
If she bought a 500 pages book and wrote on 150 pages, the number of empty pages remaining is 500-150 = <<500-150=380>>380 pages.
She then wrote on 30/100*380 = <<30/100*380=114>>114 pages
The number of remaining empty pages is 380-114 = <<380-114=266>>266 pages.
When she spilled coffee on the remaining empty pages, the number of damaged pages was 20/100*266 = <<20/100*266=266/5>>266/5
The number of empty pages remaining that she could write on is 266-266/5 = <<266-266/5=1064/5>>1064/5 pages
#### 1064/5
